The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in China trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the last close.  The  Shanghai Composite Index , which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, gained 23.11, or 0.8 percent, to
2,888.57. The  CSI 300 Index  added 1 percent to 3,178.85.  Banks:  China ordered banks to set aside larger reserves
for the fifth time this year, draining cash from the financial
system to limit inflation and asset-bubble risks in the world’s
fastest-growing major economy. The ratio will increase 50 basis
points starting Nov. 29, the central bank said.  Bank of Communications Co . (601328 CH) closed unchanged at
5.78 yuan per share.   Agricultural Bank of China Ltd.  (601288
CH) gained 0.4 percent to 2.68 yuan apiece.  Ping An Insurance (Group) Company of China Ltd  (601318 CH):
President Louis Cheung resigned effect March 18, 2011, for
“personal reasons” and will be replaced by Ren Huichuan. The
stock rose 0.1 percent to 57.71 yuan.  Changsha Zoomlion Heavy Industry Science and Technology
Development Co.  (000157 CH): The company has got approval from
the China Securities Regulatory Commission to list its stock in
Hong Kong. The company rose 5 percent to 13.23 yuan per share.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
